<title>SWITZERLAND: Meningitis epidemic kills 1,506 in Africa.</title>
<headline>Meningitis epidemic kills 1,506 in Africa.</headline>
<dateline>GENEVA 1997-03-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>A meningitis epidemic in Africa has now claimed 1,506 victims, the World Health Organisation (WHO) said on Friday.</p>
<p>The epidemic has struck 11,175 people and of the seven countries reporting cases the hardest hit is Burkina Faso, where 724 patients out of 5,571 have died.</p>
<p>Other countries reporting outbreaks were Benin, Gambia, Ghana, Mali, Niger and Togo.</p>
<p>The United Nations health agency last month launched an emergency appeal to donor countries to raise $6.3 million to purchase and distribute vaccines.</p>
<p>So far it has only received about half this amount, a WHO spokesman said.</p>
